{{Use Australian English|date=September 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox institute | name = Bio21 Institute | image = Bio21 lobby.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = The lobby of Bio21 Institute | latin_name = | motto = | founder = | established = {{start date and age|2002|df=y}} | mission = | focus = | president = | ceo = | chairman = | head_label = Director | head = Michael Parker | faculty = [[University of Melbourne]] | adjunct_faculty = | staff = | key_people = | budget = | endowment = | debt = | num_members = | subsidiaries = | owner = | non-profit_slogan = | former_name = | location = [[Flemington Road, Melbourne|Flemington Road]], {{VICcity|Parkville}} | city = [[Melbourne]] | state = [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] | province = | country = Australia | coor = {{coord|-37.7983|144.9575|display=title,inline|format=dms}} | address = | website = {{URL|www.bio21.unimelb.edu.au/}} | dissolved = | footnotes = }} The '''Bio21 Institute of Molecular Science and Biotechnology''', abbreviated as the '''Bio21 Institute''', is an Australian scientific research [[research institute|institute]] focuses on the study of basic science and applied biotechnology. The Bio21 Institute is based at the [[University of Melbourne]] on [[Flemington Road, Melbourne|Flemington Road]] in {{VICcity|Parkville}}, [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]].
The Institute is managed by the University of Melbourne and is supported by funding from the Victorian Government.
==History== Established in 2002 and officially opened in 2005, the research centre conducts interdisciplinary learning and houses research groups specializing in biochemistry, cell biology, chemistry, and other life sciences. Bio21 accommodates over 500 research scientists, students and industry participants, making it one of the largest biotechnology research centres in Australia.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bio21.unimelb.edu.au/about-bio21 |title=About Bio21 |date=2015 |accessdate=13 September 2016 |website=www.bio21.unimelb.edu.au |publisher= |last= |first= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502095837/http://www.bio21.unimelb.edu.au/about-bio21 |archivedate=2 May 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>{{self-published inline|date=September 2016}}
In September 2006, Bio21 formed a partnership with Australian-based global bio-pharmaceutical company [[CSL Limited]]. 50 scientists from CSL were relocated to participate in activities at the Bio21. The goal of the partnership was for Bio21 to gain the expertise of industry professionals and for CSL to gain access to state-of-the-art equipment.<ref>{{cite news |title=CSL scientists move to Melbourne Uni |work=NineMSN |agency=[[Australian Associated Press|AAP]] |date=2006 |url=http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=65820 |accessdate=1 January 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060920095034/http://news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=65820 |archivedate=20 September 2006 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Scott |first=Rebecca |title=Bio21 Inst to host CSL scientists |journal=UniNews |volume=15 |number=17 |publisher=[[University of Melbourne]] |date=2006 |url=http://uninews.unimelb.edu.au/news/3671/ |accessdate=1 January 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080912023818/http://uninews.unimelb.edu.au/news/3671/ |archivedate=12 September 2008 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
